\c 10
\p
\v 1 And these are the generations of the sons of Noah, Shem, Ham, and Japheth. And sons were born to them after the flood.
\v 2 The sons of Japheth were Gomer and Magon and Madai and Javan and Tubal and Meshech and Tiras.
\v 3 And the Sons of Gomer were Ashkenaz and Riphath and Togarmah.
\v 4 The sons of Javan were Elishah and Tarshish, Kittim and Dodanim.
\v 5 From these the Islands of the nations spread out according to their lands, each man to his own language and to his own tribe in their nations.
\v 6 And the sons of Ham were Cush and Mizraim and Put and Canaan.
\v 7 The sons of Cush were Seba and Havilah and Sabtah and Raama and Sabteca. And the sons of Raamah were Shebah and Dedan.
\v 8 And Cush fathered Nimrod. He started the might man on the earth.
\v 9 He was a mighty hunter before the Lord so it is said, â€œLike Nimrod the mighty hunter before the Lord.
\v 10 And the beginning of his kingdom was Babel and Erech and Accad and Calneh, in the land of Shinar.
\v 11 From that land he went out to Assyria and he built Nineveh and Rehoboth-Ir and Calah,
\v 12 and Resen between Nineveh and Calah. That is the great city.
\v 13 And Mizraim fathered Ludim and Anamim and Lehabim and Naphtuhim
\v 14 and Pathrusim and Casluhim (from whom came the Philistines) and Caphtorim.
\v 15 And Canaan fathered Sidon his firstborn, and Heth
\v 16 and the Jebusite and the Amorite and the Girgashite
\v 17 and the Hivvite and the Arkite and the Sinite
\v 18 and the Arvadite and the Zemarite and the Hamathite and after the familes of the Canaanites scattered.
\v 19 And the border of Canaan was from Sidon to Gerar as far as Gaza as you go to Somdom and Gomorah and Admah and Zeboiim as far as Lasha.
\v 20 These are the sons of Ham according to their familes, by their languages, in their lands, in their nations.
\v 21 And to Shem was born, even he was the father of the Eberites, the older brother of Japheth.
\v 22 The sons of Shem were Elam and Asshur and Arpachshad and Lud and Aram.
\v 23 The Sons of Aram were Uz and Hul and Gether and Mash.
\v 24 Arpachshad fathered Shelah and Shelah fathered Eber.
\v 25 And to Eber were born two sons. The name of the first was Peleg for in his days the earth was divided and the name of his brother was Joktan.
\v 26 And Joktan fathered Almodad and Sheleph and Hazarmaveth and Jerah
\v 27 and Hadoram and Uzal and Diklah
\v 28 and Obal and Abimael and Sheba
\v 29 and Ophir and Havilah and Jobab. All these were sons of Joktan.
\v 30 And their settlement was from Mesha as you come to Sephar, the hill country to the east.
\v 31 These are the sons of Shem by their families by their languages in their lands by their nations.
\v 32 These are the families of the sons of Noah by their accounts in their nations and from these the nations were spread out on the earth after the flood.